 4ebdba5b-ba49-4ab5-b2c1-d74a80ca85b7.c9ce48f4-fcc6-4d13-8725-dbf61b635556.description=e0abeb09-a4b4-4a85-b20d-a6a449228eb5.5d43e991-455e-415a-ad3b-fa46ecb811d0.description 4ebdba5b-ba49-4ab5-b2c1-d74a80ca85b7.d9b65876-befb-4850-b8ea-7e176ee9a229.description=e0abeb09-a4b4-4a85-b20d-a6a449228eb5.ad8d11b3-bfc2-4306-b42f-c19f5a483233.description 4ebdba5b-ba49-4ab5-b2c1-d74a80ca85b7.description=<pre>
 Purpose

Performs a full database export on a source database instance that will be used to refresh a defined target database server.

 Description

This workflow performs a full database export using Oracle's Data Pump utility. It automatically detects which ORACLE_HOME and ORACLE_SID is to be used in performing the required Data Pump tasks. Workflow user identifies which server the tasks is to run on as it also identifies which database instance to use on the deployment page. It uses a parameter file and entries are properly validated. Oracle database and O/S versions are verified if it belongs to the supported platform prior to performing Data Pump tasks. Encryption, compression, size of dump files are handled by defining proper entries in the parameter file.

 Usage instructions

User supplies all the necessary required data in the deployment parameter page. The target directory in the parameter file represents the path associated with the Oracle directory object and must be pre-created prior to execution of this workflow. This is the location where the export Data Pump dump files are to be placed and read by the target database server. Both the source and target database servers must have read and write access on the defined target server. The workflow will use its default values whenever optional fields are not populated. If the user left the Data Pump Parameter File field blank, the workflow will generate a parameter file to be used based on readily filled data on the deployment page, and workflow generated values.


 Dependencies

SA Agents must be installed on all target servers. Target Directory supplied in the Deployment Page must be pre-created in the operating system. Supplied Oracle user must have access to the provided Target Directory. Oracle directory to be used by Data Pump must exist prior workflow execution. Oracle user must have read/write access to Oracle object directory associated path.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 Instance.Name - No description
 Instance.os user - No description
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 Server.Become User - No description
 Target Directory - *Required\: Directory where Data Pump dump and Parameter files are to be staged on target database server. Must be known to the Oracle Instance.

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Statistics - *Optional\: A parameter comparable to STATISTICS is not needed. Statistics are always saved for tables.
 Reuse - *Optional\: If it is set as "Y", it overwrites destination dump file if it exists Default\: [N].
 Oracle DB User Password - *Optional\: Required only if the DB User Password should not be '/ as sysdba'.
 Show Log File - *Optional\: Will print the export log file contents to console and history pages if set to True. Default value is False.
 Schema - *Optional\: Comma separated list of schemas to export. REQUIRED if Data Pump Parameter File not specified.
 Parallel - *Optional\: Change the number of active workers for current job.
 Oracle DB User - *Optional\: Database User account if other than sysdba. Must have required privileges or workflow will fail.
 Compression - *Optional\: Valid settings are 'ALL', 'NONE', 'DATA_ONLY', 'METADATA_ONLY'. Default setting is 'ALL'.
 Metrics - No description
 File Size - *Optional\: How large should the individual dump files be? Multiple files will be generated if the dump is larger than the File Size.
 Full - *Optional\: Set to 'Y' to do a complete database export, 'N' when exporting schemas. Mapping set in workflow and should not be modified. Default is 'Y'
 Flashback Time - *Optional\: Time used to find the closest corresponding SCN value. Format\: 'DD-MM-YYYY HH24\:MI\:SS' or 'systimestamp'
 Include - *Optional\: Enables you to filter the metadata that is exported by specifying objects and object types for the current export mode.
 The specified objects and all their dependent objects are exported. Example\: TABLE\:"LIKE'TABLE_NAME%'",VIEW\:"LIKE'VIEW_NAME%'"
 Data Pump Parameter File - *Optional\: Parameter File used with the Data Pump Import Utility. Default parameter values will be generated if Parameter File none provided.
 Oracle Account - *Optional\: Oracle user that owns the ORACLE_HOME on target database server. Required if inventory does not exist. Left blank for Windows.
 Encryption Mode - *Optional\: Encryption Mode to be used on export, Encryption Password is required to be set if encryption is used. Valid settings are 'DUAL', 'PASSWORD', 'TRANSPARENT'. No value defaults to no encryption.
 Ignorable Oracle Errors - No description
 Job Name - *Optional\: Name of export job to create.
 Content - No description
 Encryption Password - *Optional\: Only required when Encryption Mode is set.
 Exclude - *Optional\: Exclude specific object types.
Example\: TABLE\:"LIKE'TABLE_NAME%'",VIEW\:"LIKE'VIEW_NAME%'"
 Flashback SCN - *Optional\: SCN used to reset session snapshot.

 Additional Documentation

Additional information, including the _HP Database and Middleware Automation Support Matrix_ and solution pack user guides, are available via HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the RESOURCES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
</pre> 4ebdba5b-ba49-4ab5-b2c1-d74a80ca85b7.e894bdd8-8b25-4842-9cbc-d029d3cb89c7.description=Description\:
